TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Comparison of the Multiple Dispatch and M/M/c Priority Queueing Models of Police Patrol
AU  - Green, Linda
AU  - Kolesar, Peter
Y1  - 1984/06/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.30.6.665
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.30.6.665
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 665
EP  - 670
VL  - 30
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In many cities, a substantial fraction of calls for police service require more than one patrol car. We compare Green's multiple dispatch queueing model to several M/M/c-based approximations for multiple car dispatching that are obtained by adjusting the parameters. We found that none of the approximate models yields consistently reliable results under a broad range of conditions. The best approximations are produced by reducing the actual number of servers. Increasing the call rate gives the worst results.
AB  - In many cities, a substantial fraction of calls for police service require more than one patrol car. We compare Green's multiple dispatch queueing model to several M/M/c-based approximations for multiple car dispatching that are obtained by adjusting the parameters. We found that none of the approximate models yields consistently reliable results under a broad range of conditions. The best approximations are produced by reducing the actual number of servers. Increasing the call rate gives the worst results.
